From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] media: cedrus: add suniv F1C100s variant

The suniv F1C100s/F1C200s carries a first-generation Video Engine
(revision 0x1663, read from VE_VERSION).  The BSP treats it exactly
like the A10 class: libVE groups it with 0x1623 (A13) and 0x1625 (A20)
in the enable/disable paths ((version & ~0x40) == 0x1623), and
libawh264 pairs it with the A20 for the external prediction-buffer
handling.  It is *not* a V3s-class engine, despite the SoC's sun8iw8
family branding.

Model the variant on the A10 generation:

  - MPEG2 + H264 only.  No UNTILED: the engine writes the native
    MB32-tiled NV12 only (which is exactly what the F1C200s DE1
    front-end scans out); no VP8 as it is untested on this part.
  - CEDRUS_QUIRK_EXTERNAL_PRED_BUFFERS: no internal deblock and
    intra-prediction SRAM (see the corresponding cedrus_h264 commit).
  - CEDRUS_QUIRK_NO_DRAM_MODE_CONFIG: in-package 16-bit DDR, the BSP
    leaves the VE_MODE DRAM field at its power-on default.
  - mod_rate 297 MHz: PLL_VE's validated operating point on the
    F1C200s (PLL range is 30-600 MHz per the F1C200s user manual);
    requires ve_clk to be parented to PLL_VE with rate propagation.

Note on DMA addressing: unlike the A10 class, the suniv VE consumes
full 32-bit physical addresses (DRAM lives at 0x80000000 on this SoC
and decode demonstrably lands in the right buffers with unadjusted
vb2 dma addresses; the BSP ION path likewise hands the raw CMA handle
to the engine).  Do NOT add the compatible to the sunxi_mbus notifier
list - a dma offset would shift every address by -0x80000000.

Also document the new compatible in the DT binding.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 .../bindings/media/allwinner,sun4i-a10-video-engine.yaml |  1 +
 drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c              | 13 +++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 14 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c
@@ -647,6 +647,14 @@
 	.mod_rate	= 600000000,
 };
 
+static const struct cedrus_variant suniv_f1c100s_cedrus_variant = {
+	.capabilities	= CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_MPEG2_DEC |
+			  CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_H264_DEC,
+	.quirks		= CEDRUS_QUIRK_EXTERNAL_PRED_BUFFERS |
+			  CEDRUS_QUIRK_NO_DRAM_MODE_CONFIG,
+	.mod_rate	= 297000000,
+};
+
 static const struct of_device_id cedrus_dt_match[] = {
 	{
 		.compatible = "allwinner,sun4i-a10-video-engine",
@@ -692,6 +700,10 @@
 		.compatible = "allwinner,sun50i-h6-video-engine",
 		.data = &sun50i_h6_cedrus_variant,
 	},
+	{
+		.compatible = "allwinner,suniv-f1c100s-video-engine",
+		.data = &suniv_f1c100s_cedrus_variant,
+	},
 	{ /* sentinel */ }
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, cedrus_dt_match);
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/media/allwinner,sun4i-a10-video-engine.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/media/allwinner,sun4i-a10-video-engine.yaml
@@ -24,6 +24,7 @@
       - allwinner,sun50i-a64-video-engine
       - allwinner,sun50i-h5-video-engine
       - allwinner,sun50i-h6-video-engine
+      - allwinner,suniv-f1c100s-video-engine
 
   reg:
     maxItems: 1
